description:
Modern, affordable hotel opposite London Victoria

Opposite Victoria
This modern 4-star hotel places you right opposite Victoria Station, one of Londons key transport hubs. As well as being just steps from Tube, Overground, and mainline train services, youll be a 15-minute stroll from Buckingham Palace and St. Jamess Park.

2 great galleries
You'll be a 20-minute walk or brisk Tube ride from Tate Britain with its unequaled collection of historical and contemporary British art. For a full-blown art excursion, catch the catamaran at nearby Millbank Millennium Pier, which will ferry you to Tate Modern.

Check in with cookies
At DoubleTree by Hilton London Victoria you'll be greeted with a warm chocolate-chip cookie on check-in. For something more substantial, visit 2 Bridge Place restaurant, which serves up modern European dishes. There's a fitness center as well as a business center on site. Free WiFi is available in public areas.

Contemporary comforts
Guestrooms soothe with comfy beds and jumbo hypo-allergenic down pillows. They also feature LCD TVs with satellite channels, minibars, free WiFi, and desks with ergonomic chairs great for business travelers.

HOTEL_AMENITY.value:
The hotel has a 24-hour front desk, and 24-hour business center with a technology helpdesk. Meeting facilities include conference rooms, exhibit space, banquet facilities, and rooms for small groups.

This London property also offers a restaurant, 2 Bridge Place, serving breakfast and dinner daily.

DINING.value:
2 Bridge Place Restaurant - This smart, contemporary venue is divided from the lobby by artistic glass partitions and serves varied a la carte Mediterranean dishes for dinner, as well as a full breakfast daily. The menu varies monthly but always includes a range of fish and meat options.


DoubleTree by Hilton London Victoria Bar - This glass-fronted bar overlooks the street and serves a range of draught beers and bar snacks. A large flatscreen TV shows major sports events.

Bustling transport hub Victoria Station is steps away, while must-photograph attractions like Buckingham Palace and the Houses of Parliament are within walking distance. Guestrooms offer free WiFi and premium bedding for a good night's sleep.
